Subject: Re: [T2] sliding door step attachs how?

On Mon, Dec 15, 2003 at 05:15:49PM -0800, D&C Tuinstra wrote:
> Hi!  I just acquired a side step for under the sliding door.  I have a 78
> westy.  Yesterday we tried it and it slid into the jack tubes just fine.
> However,  I don't see any fasteners or holes for any or???     Anyone out
> there have one?  If so how do they stay on the bus?

on my 79 I was given a side step from a fellow listee. It slides in
the jack points and there is a piece of flat stock on the bottom of
the tubes that enter the jackpoint. These pieces have a metal dowel
that should go into the hole on the under side of the jackpoint. HTH.

